    <item>
      <title>New Everquest Game Client?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3800#M3800</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I have played Everquest for more years then I care to admit.  I have left, come back, left again, come back again, etc.  During those times away, I have played the other MMOs (World of Warcraft, Everquest 2, Dark Age of Camelot, City of Villains, Dungeons and Dragons Online, and others).  They all had their things that were nice, and they all had things that were bad.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The thing that amazes me is that out of all of the MMOs on the market today, Everquest still has the best core-system.  Now understand, I am NOT saying that Everquest looks the best, runs the best, NOR has the best user interface.  In actuality, it does not.  But, the core system of Everquest seems to be the best.  It might be the fact that it is six years old and has had time to develop slowly.  Who knows, but there is something about Everquest that is worth coming back to.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;That brings me to the point of this thread... Everytime I come back to Everquest, I play the game and think &amp;quot;hmmm not quite as nice as I remembered it.&amp;quot;  The simple fact is that the game client is out-dated.  It's just plain old.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So, my question is this SoE... Will there EVER be a new game client created for Everquest in the future?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Wouldn't it be worth the time to devote one of the upcoming expansions solely to creating a brand new game client from scratch that is on par with the rest of the MMO industry?  You don't have to change the server, the rules of the game, or anything core to the system.  Just make a new game client.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It seems to me that if Everquest was to come out with a brand new game client that was on par with the MMOs coming out today, more people would come back to Everquest.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Call me crazy, but I just do not believe that you can expect to keep running Everquest on this out-dated game client for ever.  Eventually, it will just get too old and be more of a niche game then anything.  Already, I have friends that are new to the MMO craze that absolutely refuse to try Everquest solely based on the way it looks feels.  That's potential customers that were lost ONLY because the game client is out-dated.  I know I can't be alone in thinking this way...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
