      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I guess since this thread is dieing a horrible death that it means SoE is happy with the current state of the EQ game client, and there is no hope of it ever being updated in the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;So... what we got now is what we have next year.. the year after.. and the year after that...  Just a new expansion twice a year until there are not enough customers left to warrant another one.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All sarcasm aside, I have to say that this is the biggest &amp;quot;drop the ball&amp;quot; that any software manufacturer has ever done in the history of the gaming industry.  Before you ignore this thread and move on, please hear me out cause I say this with love.. not hate.  This is what is called constructive criticism.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sony Online Entertainment has the single best and LARGEST MMORPG content in the history of MMORPGs.  You have a proven product, an already created fan following, and everything you need to continue to dominate the industry.  All you have to do is spend ONE YEAR making a whole new game client that utilizes your existing servers, and you will be able to retake your lost customers from World of Warcraft and continue to dominate the industry for another six years at least.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Other software publishers would kill to have the advantage that Sony Online Entertainment has with Everquest.  The competitors have to create everything from scratch and HOPE that they can get a foot in the door long enough to create a fan following.  Sony Online Entertainment already has that and then some, but they won't make a new game client.  It doesn't make sense.  It really just doesn't make sense.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The only thing I can come up with is that somebody in charge wants Everquest to fail.  But, why?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Just admit it already.  Nobody will hold anybody accountable for making the wrong decissions.  Everquest 2 was a failure.  But, Everquest 1 does NOT have to be a failure.  Even if you was to put Everquest 2's game client on top of the already existing Everquest 1 server environment, you would already have a better game then Everquest 2.  With out a doubt.  Hands down.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you don't believe me, then do one of your poles that Sony Online Entertainment has done in the past.  Ask the public &amp;quot;Would you consider coming back to Everquest 1 if we used the Everquest 2 game client with the Everquest 1 server rules, lore, and existing content?&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I bet everything I have that at least 80% will answer YES.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
