      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes.  I am aware they have updated the game client in the past, but there is noway anybody can argue that Everquest looks as good as World of Warcraft, Everquest 2, or Dungeons and Dragons Online.  In comparison, the characters and the majority of the zones look way out-dated.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, even though the game client has been updated to allow for more user friendly control and modification, it still is not on par with the games coming out right now.  The controls feel clunky after playing a game like World of Warcraft.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please understand that this is NOT an attempt to put Everquest down.  On the contrary, I am just praying that Sony Online Entertainment will take the time to fully upgrade the game client to the current MMO industries standards.  I would hate to see SoE allow Everquest to just die off.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Another thing that bothers me, and I honestly have NO CLUE how you would solve this problem is the simple fact that someone starting new in Everquest today would be years behind anybody who has been playing the game for a long time now.  How does a completely new person to Everquest get to level 70 with 400+ AAs on their own, so that they can then get in to an already running guild.  It's not like there are thousands of &amp;quot;new players&amp;quot; to level up and gear up with in the game anymore.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;These are just my concerns, and the only reason I even bother to mention them is because I have been a fan of the game for many years.  The future of Everquest does mean something to me.  It's like driving past your old high school and noticing that the place is going down hill fast.  You kinda feel a part of you die inside.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
